<bibRefCitation id="EFED05D45607FFBAFDA5FA07FC8DFA4D" author="Logunov, D. V. &amp; Azarkina, G. N." box="[551,893,1508,1535]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" pagination="1 - 126" refId="ref7910" refString="Logunov, D. V. &amp; Azarkina, G. N. (2018) Redefinition and partial revision of the genus Stenaelurillus Simon, 1886 (Arachnida, Araneae, Salticidae). European Journal of Taxonomy, 2018, 1 - 126. https: // doi. org / 10.5852 / ejt. 2018.43" type="journal article" year="2018">Logunov and Azarkina (2018)</bibRefCitation>
, whose terminology for components of the male palp we follow.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3662BAE5607FFBAFF45F9CEFB14F844" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BC378255607FFBAFF45F9CEFB14F844" blockId="1.[151,1437,1472,2039]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
<emphasis id="B908A4375607FFBAFF45F9CEFECBF9F5" bold="true" box="[199,315,1580,1606]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Remarks.</emphasis>
No phylogeny has yet been proposed for 
<taxonomicName id="4C7C03A65607FFBAFCC8F9CEFC16F9F5" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1886" box="[842,998,1580,1606]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Stenaelurillus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B908A4375607FFBAFCC8F9CEFC16F9F5" box="[842,998,1580,1606]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Stenaelurillus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, nor formal species groups, making it sometimes difficult to choose a focus of diagnostic comparisons for new species. As a provisional guide for identification, however, the species known from the Indian subcontinent can be sorted based on colour pattern. One set of species are primarily black and white, having a white male clypeus, striped carapace, abdomen (usually) with large white spots, and legs with a black background.These include 
<taxonomicName id="4C7C03A65607FFBAFCECF95EFEBAF948" authority="Sebastian, Sankaran, Malamel &amp; Joseph, 2015" authorityName="Sebastian, Sankaran, Malamel &amp; Joseph" authorityYear="2015" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Stenaelurillus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albus">
<emphasis id="B908A4375607FFBAFCECF95EFBBAF965" box="[878,1098,1724,1750]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Stenaelurillus albus</emphasis>
Sebastian, Sankaran, Malamel &amp; Joseph, 2015
</taxonomicName>
; 
<taxonomicName id="4C7C03A65607FFBAFED5F902FCCBF949" authority="(Biswas &amp; Biswas, 1992)" baseAuthorityName="Biswas &amp; Biswas" baseAuthorityYear="1992" box="[343,827,1760,1786]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Stenaelurillus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="arambagensis">
<emphasis id="B908A4375607FFBAFED5F902FDE0F949" box="[343,528,1760,1786]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">S. arambagensis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFED05D45607FFBAFDA2F902FCC3F949" author="Biswas, B. &amp; Biswas, K." box="[544,819,1760,1786]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" pagination="357 - 500" refId="ref7394" refString="Biswas, B. &amp; Biswas, K. (1992) Araneae: Spiders. State Fauna Series 3: Fauna of West Bengal, 3, 357 - 500." type="journal article" year="1992">Biswas &amp; Biswas, 1992</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
; 
<taxonomicName id="4C7C03A65607FFBAFCC5F902FAEBF949" authority="Logunov &amp; Azarkina, 2018" authorityName="Logunov &amp; Azarkina" authorityYear="2018" box="[839,1307,1760,1787]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Stenaelurillus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="belihuloya">
<emphasis id="B908A4375607FFBAFCC5F902FC2AF949" box="[839,986,1760,1786]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">S. belihuloya</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFED05D45607FFBAFC60F903FAEBF949" author="Logunov, D. V. &amp; Azarkina, G. N." box="[994,1307,1760,1787]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" pagination="1 - 126" refId="ref7910" refString="Logunov, D. V. &amp; Azarkina, G. N. (2018) Redefinition and partial revision of the genus Stenaelurillus Simon, 1886 (Arachnida, Araneae, Salticidae). European Journal of Taxonomy, 2018, 1 - 126. https: // doi. org / 10.5852 / ejt. 2018.43" type="journal article" year="2018">Logunov &amp; Azarkina, 2018</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
; 
<taxonomicName id="4C7C03A65607FFBAFAA5F902FD25F8AD" authority="Prajapati, Murthappa, Sankaran &amp; Sebastian, 2016" authorityName="Prajapati, Murthappa, Sankaran &amp; Sebastian" authorityYear="2016" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Stenaelurillus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gabrieli">
<emphasis id="B908A4375607FFBAFAA5F902FA6DF949" box="[1319,1437,1760,1786]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">S. gabrieli</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFED05D45607FFBAFF15F8E6FD25F8AD" author="Prajapati, D. A. &amp; Murthappa, P. S. &amp; Sankaran, P. M. &amp; Sebastian, PA" box="[151,725,1796,1822]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" pagination="321 - 334" refId="ref7968" refString="Prajapati, D. A., Murthappa, P. S., Sankaran, P. M. &amp; Sebastian, PA. (2016) Two new species of Stenaelurillus Simon, 1886 from India (Araneae: Salticidae: Aelurillina). Zootaxa, 4171 (2), 321 - 334. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4171.2.5" type="journal article" year="2016">Prajapati, Murthappa, Sankaran &amp; Sebastian, 2016</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
; 
<taxonomicName id="4C7C03A65607FFBAFD62F8E6FB35F8AC" authority="Das, Malik &amp; Vidhel, 2015" authorityName="Das, Malik &amp; Vidhel" authorityYear="2015" box="[736,1221,1796,1823]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Stenaelurillus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jagannathae">
<emphasis id="B908A4375607FFBAFD62F8E6FC79F8AD" box="[736,905,1796,1822]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">S. jagannathae</emphasis>
Das, Malik &amp; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFED05D45607FFBAFBB3F8E6FB35F8AC" author="Vidhel, B. P. &amp; Malik, S. &amp; Sabata, B. C. &amp; Das, S. K." box="[1073,1221,1796,1823]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" pagination="2332 - 2336" refId="ref8282" refString="Vidhel, B. P., Malik, S., Sabata, B. C. &amp; Das, S. K. (2015) A new spider species of the genus Stenaelurillus Simon, 1886 (Araneae: Salticidae: Aelurillinae) from India. International Journal of Science and Research (IJSR), 4, 2332 - 2336." type="journal article" year="2015">Vidhel, 2015</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
; 
<taxonomicName id="4C7C03A65607FFBAFB53F8E6FE9BF8F1" authority="Ali &amp; Maddison, 2018" authorityName="Ali &amp; Maddison" authorityYear="2018" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Stenaelurillus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mardanicus">
<emphasis id="B908A4375607FFBAFB53F8E6FA81F8AD" box="[1233,1393,1796,1822]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">S. mardanicus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFED05D45607FFBAFAFAF8E6FE9BF8F1" author="Ali, P. A. &amp; Maddison, W. P. &amp; Zahid, M. &amp; Butt, A." pageId="1" pageNumber="2" pagination="1 - 15" refId="ref7334" refString="Ali, P. A., Maddison, W. P., Zahid, M. &amp; Butt, A. (2018) New chrysilline and aelurilline jumping spiders from Pakistan (Araneae, Salticidae). ZooKeys, 783, 1 - 15. https: // doi. org / 10.3897 / zookeys. 783.21985" type="journal article" year="2018">Ali &amp; Maddison, 2018</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
; and 
<taxonomicName id="4C7C03A65607FFBAFE27F8CAFD3CF8F0" authority="Simon, 1885" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1885" box="[421,716,1832,1859]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Stenaelurillus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="triguttatus">
<emphasis id="B908A4375607FFBAFE27F8CAFDC5F8F1" box="[421,565,1832,1858]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">S. triguttatus</emphasis>
Simon, 1885
</taxonomicName>
. In contrast, a second set of 
<taxonomicName id="4C7C03A65607FFBAFB80F8CAFB6EF8F1" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1886" box="[1026,1182,1832,1858]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Stenaelurillus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B908A4375607FFBAFB80F8CAFB6EF8F1" box="[1026,1182,1832,1858]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Stenaelurillus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<collectingCountry id="F36B38B55607FFBAFB42F8CAFB0AF8F1" box="[1216,1274,1832,1858]" name="India" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">India</collectingCountry>
are distinctive for having a male abdomen with lateral fringes, including 
<taxonomicName id="4C7C03A65607FFBAFC9BF8AEFB4DF8D5" authority="Logunov, 2020" authorityName="Logunov" authorityYear="2020" box="[793,1213,1868,1895]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Stenaelurillus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="indicus">
<emphasis id="B908A4375607FFBAFC9BF8AEFBFBF8D5" box="[793,1035,1868,1894]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Stenaelurillus indicus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFED05D45607FFBAFB93F8AFFB4DF8D5" author="Logunov, D. V." box="[1041,1213,1868,1895]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" pagination="201 - 214" refId="ref7861" refString="Logunov, D. V. (2020) Further notes on the genus Stenaelurillus Simon, 1885 from India (Araneae: Salticidae). Zootaxa, 4899 (1), 201 - 214. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4899.1.11" type="journal article" year="2020">Logunov, 2020</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
; 
<taxonomicName id="4C7C03A65607FFBAFB45F8AEFEBAF839" authority="Caleb &amp; Mathai, 2016" authorityName="Caleb &amp; Mathai" authorityYear="2016" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Stenaelurillus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="metallicus">
<emphasis id="B908A4375607FFBAFB45F8AEFB25F8D5" box="[1223,1237,1868,1894]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B908A4375607FFBAFB60F8AEFAA5F8D5" box="[1250,1365,1868,1894]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">metallicus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFED05D45607FFBAFAD9F8AEFEBAF839" author="Caleb, J. T. D. &amp; Mathai, M. T." pageId="1" pageNumber="2" pagination="185 - 188" refId="ref7473" refString="Caleb, J. T. D. &amp; Mathai, M. T. (2016) A new jumping spider of the genus Stenaelurillus Simon, 1886 from India (Araneae: Salticidae: Aelurillina). Zootaxa, 4103 (2), 185 - 188. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4103.2.10" type="journal article" year="2016">Caleb &amp; Mathai, 2016</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C7C03A65607FFBAFE00F892FCFEF839" authority="Caleb &amp; Mathai, 2014" authorityName="Caleb &amp; Mathai" authorityYear="2014" box="[386,782,1904,1931]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Stenaelurillus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sarojinae">
<emphasis id="B908A4375607FFBAFE00F892FE60F839" box="[386,400,1904,1930]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B908A4375607FFBAFE1CF893FDF7F839" box="[414,519,1905,1930]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">sarojinae</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFED05D45607FFBAFD8DF892FCFEF839" author="Caleb, J. T. D. &amp; Mathai, M. T." box="[527,782,1904,1930]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" pagination="63 - 71" refId="ref7426" refString="Caleb, J. T. D. &amp; Mathai, M. T. (2014) Description of some interesting jumping spiders (Araneae: Salticidae) from South India. India Journal of Entomology and Zoology Studies, 2, 63 - 71." type="journal article" year="2014">Caleb &amp; Mathai, 2014</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. These species also share a dark male clypeus, a colourful abdomen with spots smaller or absent, legs with a brown to orange background, and a palpal femur with a ventral process located distally near patella. One of the new species described below is among the black and white species, the others among the colourful fringed species. We also report on a new population of 
<taxonomicName id="4C7C03A65607FFBAFBDDF83EFB2DF845" authorityName="Logunov" authorityYear="2001" box="[1119,1245,2012,2038]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Stenaelurillus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="marusiki">
<emphasis id="B908A4375607FFBAFBDDF83EFB2DF845" box="[1119,1245,2012,2038]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">S. marusiki</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
